            "answer_text": "Yes. You visit the site nios.ac.in. On the left hand, at the bottom of the page, you can see a box.. Click on the, \u2018on demand examination\u2019 option. You will get options to choose from. There are separate options for i) registered and ii) non-registered student; Secondary and Sr Secondary. Click accordingly. Then click on \u2018register now\u2019 It will ask for your e-mail and password. Create one like raju9@gmail.com etc. Don\u2019t provide your existing e-mail. Lest you can not login. Once you successfully login, the software will navigate you to book the exam dates. Your exam centre can be choosen by you. It may be the regional office of your state or HQ noida or any other, if available. Book your exam dates. Exam pattern is not pre-designed like in nios regular exams. You can study the same book which is prescribed for nios regular students. Now you can book your exam dates. On-demand exams are not held during nios regular exam. All the best!!! ",
